name: BrewDog Shepherds Bush

items.summary: Lots of people like this place

description: Our thirteenth bar worldwide is now open in West London! BrewDog Shepherd's Bush, serves up 40 craft beers on tap alongside heaps more bottles and cans in the fridges and a BBQ menu of some super tasty food courtesy of Texas Joe.

pageInfo.description: BrewDog is Scotland's largest independent brewery. Our bars are beacons of hope for craft beer fans across the country. Come and join us in our Cathedrals of hops and glory!

items.text: wow. such beers
Great BBQ food! If you can't decide on a beer after a few tastes, get a tasting tray :)
Has a wider range than BrewDog's other London pubs.  It's a big space yet retains atmosphere.  Great staff and old-school arcade machines.  Serves good quality US-style BBQ food.
DRINK IT ALL. ALL OF THE BEER.
Huge range of both Brewdog and non-Brewdog beer + pinball tables in the back!
All the beers :D
Loads of great guest beers on the multitude of taps. Good usage of smaller size glasses. Be sure to try as much as possible. The BBQ food is fairly poor however.
If you like IPAs, try the Jackhammer.
Love the table service
Fake lager is pretty good if you're a lout like me.
Beer is awesome. 40 taps. The staff will help and advise.
Beer tastes like ass; take it from a northern lass. Although the decor and arcade games are pretty cool...all in all, good vibe, shame about the beer.
Best beer selection in the area. Always something new to try
It's a Brew Dog and, if you're seeing this as a notification alert then it's near you. Now stop wasting your time reading my tripe and go there!
Love this place. Cannot recommend the posh burger highly enough, delicious. Excellent selection of beers, as you'd expect. Spacious seating and arcade games add a chilled ambience.
Amazing choice of beers especially ales. They brew some of them. Dead pony ale has fruity original aroma. Pretty nice interior for a place like this.  Definitely a spot to visit.
